; Regression test for issue #1157: If aux_date is unspecified, actual date should be used (BZ#1157)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1157
; When %(aux_date) is used in a format string for a transaction that has no
; auxiliary/effective date, it should fall back to the actual date instead of
; returning an empty string.

2024/01/01=2024/01/15 Payee With Aux Date
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

2024/02/01 Payee Without Aux Date
    Expenses:Food    $20.00
    Assets:Cash

test reg --format '%(date) %(aux_date) %(payee)\n'
2024/01/01 2024/01/15 Payee With Aux Date
2024/01/01 2024/01/15 Payee With Aux Date
2024/02/01  Payee Without Aux Date
2024/02/01  Payee Without Aux Date
end test
